riant of   Aldred  . This form of the surname is widespread in eastern England, especially in Essex."],"variants":[{"name":"Aldred","meanings":["from the Middle English personal name <i>Al(d)red</i> or <i>El(d)red</i>, an overlap or merger of three Old English names, <i>Ealdrǣd</i> (or <i>Aldrǣd</i>), <i>Æthelrǣd</i>, and <i>Ælfrǣd</i>. Old English <i>Ealdrǣd</i> and its variant <i>Aldrǣd</i> regularly appear in Middle English as either <i>Eldred</i> or <i>Aldred</i>, depending on dialect. The pronunciation of Old English <i>Æthelrǣd</i> was often shortened, occurring in Middle English as <i>Ailred</i>, <i>Eilred</i>, <i>Alred</i>, and <i>Elred</i>. Subsequently a transitional <i>-d-</i> was inserted between the <i>l</i> and the <i>r</i>, resulting in <i>A(i)ldred</i> and <i>E(i)ldred</i>. Middle English forms of Old English <i>Ælfrǣd</i> sometimes lost the medial <i>-f-</i>, becoming <i>Alred</i> or <i>Elred</i>, and then <i>Aldred</i>, <i>Eldred</i>. All three personal names were largely obsolete by the end of the 13th century.","variant of   Audrey   2.","English:"]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":67,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Henry De Ledred was born in 1388, in Devon, England. He had at least 1 son with Mrs Henry De Ledred. He died in 1480, in England, at the age of 92."},"et":{"1388–1480":"1388–1480","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1447":"1447","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1388":"1388","Abt 1447":"umbes 1447","Abt 1400":"umbes 1400","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","Somerton, South Somerset, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerton, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1388–1480":"1388–1480","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1447":"1447","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1388":"1388","Abt 1447":"noin 1447","Abt 1400":"noin 1400","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","Somerton, South Somerset, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerton, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1388–1480":"1388–1480","1380–Female":"1380–Décédée","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1447":"1447","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1388":"1388","Abt 1447":"environ 1447","Abt 1400":"environ 1400","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","Somerton, South Somerset, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Somerton, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Henry De Ledred est né en 1388, à Devon, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs Henry De Ledred. Il est décédé en 1480, à Angleterre, à l’âge de 92 ans."},"de":{"1388–1480":"1388–1480","1380–Female":"1380–Verstorben","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1447":"1447","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1388":"1388","Abt 1447":"um 1447","Abt 1400":"um 1400","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","Somerton, South Somerset, Somerset, England, Unite